external_knowledge:
- "Favored attire categories" refer to the categories of clothing items that are rented the most frequently;
- "Body shape" refers to the different body types defined in the `body_types` table;
- "Crown jewels in a treasure chest of fashion rentals" is a metaphorical expression for the most popular or highly sought-after categories of rental items.

- 'Biggest spender' refers to the user with the highest total rental cost;
- 'Colorful tapestry' is a metaphor for the user's name, which is matched to the occasion name in the query;
- 'Occasions they celebrate' refers to the rental occasions, such as weddings or parties.

- "flourishing" refers to high performance in terms of rentals and revenue;
- "picked" refers to items being rented;
- "value they bring" refers to the revenue generated by the rentals.

- 'Treasures' refers to rental items;
- 'Voyagers' refers to users;
- 'Frequently visited' means the item has been rented more than 5 times;
- 'Highly praised' means the average rating is greater than 4.

- 'subscribed users' refers to users with a `subscription_status` of 1 (true);
- 'preferred occasions' are specific events or contexts for which users want personalized recommendations;
- 'average ratings' are calculated from the `rating` column in the `reviews` table, with a default value of 0 if no ratings are available.

'athletic' body type refers to a specific body shape or form characteristic of individuals who are physically fit and active;
Total rental cost is the sum of all costs associated with renting items;
Rental count is the number of times an item has been rented.

- "Crown jewels" refers to the most valuable or highly regarded items;
- "Highest accolades" refers to the highest ratings;
- "Fortunate souls" refers to the users who have rented the top-rated items.

- 'stars' refers to users who have given a rating of 10;
- 'showered their perfect praise' means they have given a rating of 10;
- 'wedding rentals' refers to items rented for the occasion of a wedding.

- "Seasoned travelers" refers to users who have rented items multiple times or for extended periods;
- "Delved into the treasure trove of costs" refers to the cumulative rental cost calculated over the total days rented and rental occasion;
- "Journey exceeding 10 days" refers to the total number of days a user has rented items being greater than 10;
- "Spent more than 100 on average per rental" refers to the average rental cost being greater than 100.

- "Popular enough" refers to items with at least 5 rentals;
- "Good reputation" refers to an average rating of 4 or more;
- "Revenue generated" is the total cost accumulated from rentals of the item.

- "gem stands out" refers to the item with the highest average rating;
- "most cherished" emphasizes the highest average rating;
- "reviewers" are users who have provided ratings for the rental items.

- "most beloved" refers to the highest average rating;
- "most profitable" refers to the highest total revenue;
- "most frequently chosen" refers to the highest number of rentals.

- "Danced the wedding waltz" refers to renting items for weddings;
- "Patrons" refers to users in the database;
- "Experience" refers to the number of reviews and the average rating of those reviews;
- "Loyalty points" are a measure of the user's engagement and satisfaction with the service.

- "rental enthusiasts" refers to users who have the highest number of rentals;
- "avid renters" refers to users who are among the top in terms of rental frequency;
- "spending" refers to the total cost of rentals;
- "exceeds the average expenditure" means the total rental cost is greater than the average total cost of the top-ranked users.
